text: Hernando is a common Spanish given name, equivalent to Fernando and the English Ferdinand. It may refer to: ==Places== ;Canada * Hernando Island, British Columbia ;United States * Hernando, Florida * Hernando County, Florida * Hernando, Mississippi ;Argentina * Hernando, Córdoba * Hernandos Hideaway long jetty Australia ==People== * Hernando de Soto (economist) * Hernando de Soto (explorer) * Hernando Cortes, alternate spelling of Hernán Cortés * Mila Hernando (1957–2017), Spanish diplomat ==Horse== * Hernando (horse) (1990-2013), French-trained racehorse, winner of the 1993 Prix du Jockey Club
title: Hernando
